    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle then wash your <strong>hispi</strong> <strong>cabbage[s] </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper and cut into quarters lengthways</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>hispi</strong> <strong>cabbage quarters</strong> to the pan, cut-side down, and cook for 4-5 min on each cut-side or until charred, once charred, transfer the cabbage quarters<strong> </strong>(reserve the pan!) to one side of a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!), top them with a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>and slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong> finely, then add your <strong>meat-free patty[ies] </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>most </strong>of the <strong>diced onion </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Divide the<strong> mixture</strong> into 2 per person and press it onto each<strong> skewer</strong> to form a long sausage shape and add your <strong>skewers </strong>to the other side of the baking tray[s], put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>charred hispi cabbage & meat-free seekh kebabs</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>cooked rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>garam masala </strong>and your <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>masala sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>cucumber </strong>finely</p><p>Grate the <strong>remaining cucumber</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mint sauce</strong>,<strong> cultured coconut </strong>and <strong>grated cucumber </strong>in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut & mint raita</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>diced cucumber </strong>and <strong>chopped tomato </strong>to a bowl with <strong>most </strong>of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>kachumber salad</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 3 min or until the bread is hot</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/masala-hispi-cabbage-meat-free-seekh-kebabs-with-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>charred hispi cabbage </strong>on top of the <strong>masala sauce</strong></p><p>Discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>cooked rice</strong>, <strong>meat-free seekh kebabs</strong>, <strong>coconut & mint raita</strong>, <strong>kachumber salad </strong>and the <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s] </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
